
Privacy Policy for Converto
Effective Date: June 22, 2026

Thank you for choosing to be part of our community at Converto ("we", "us", "our"). We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy notice, or our practices with regard to your personal information, please contact us.

When you use our mobile application, as the case may be (the "App") and more generally, use any of our services (the "Services", which include the App), we appreciate that you are trusting us with your personal information. We take your privacy very seriously. In this privacy notice, we seek to explain to you in the clearest way possible what information we collect, how we use it and what rights you have in relation to it.

1. Information We Collect
Personal Information You Disclose to Us
We do not collect, store, or process any personal data. You are not required to create an account, provide an email address, or enter any personal identifying information to use Converto.

Information Automatically Collected
When you use Converto, the app connects to the internet to fetch real-time currency exchange rates. During this process, some non-identifying information may be collected automatically by the APIs we use or the app distribution platforms (like Google Play), such as:

Device Information: Operating system version, device model, and system language (used to display the correct currency formats).
Usage Data: Diagnostic data, crash logs, and app performance metrics (to help us identify and fix bugs).
This information does not reveal your specific identity (like your name or contact information).

2. How We Use Your Information
Since we do not collect personal data, we only use the automatically collected diagnostic data to:

Provide and maintain the Service: To fetch the latest exchange rates and ensure the app runs smoothly.
Improve the App: To analyze crash reports and performance metrics to release better updates.

3. Third-Party Services
The App may use third-party services that may collect information used to identify you. Link to the privacy policy of third-party service providers used by the app:

- Google Play Services
- Currency rate APIs

4. Local Storage (Caching)
Converto uses local storage on your device to cache recent exchange rates and save your preferences (like your default currencies or watchlist). This data is stored entirely locally on your device and is never uploaded to our servers or shared with any third party. If you uninstall the app, this local data is deleted.

5. Security of Your Information
We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information (though we do not collect any). While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information you provide to us, please be aware that despite our efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable.

6. Children's Privacy
These Services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13 years of age. In the case we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we immediately delete this from our servers.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. These changes are effective immediately after they are posted on this page.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us at iumarafzalkhan@gmail.com.
